# threejs-engine-dev — Workspace Context

## Role of This Project

This is the **permanent Three.js dev harness** for all `@base` Three.js infrastructure packages. It validates `@base/player-three`, `@base/scene-builder`, `@base/camera-three`, and `@base/threejs-engine` before they are consumed by game forks. It is **not** promoted to a package — it remains a permanent integration harness.

**Current phase: 3d** — Camera strategy switching in the scene editor (third-person ↔ first-person in editor play-sim without touching game code).

## Ecosystem Topology

```
e:/Projects/
  BASE/pwa-shell/             ← shell template this was forked from
  SHARED/packages/
    engine-core/              ← @base/engine-core (linked locally)
    threejs-engine/           ← @base/threejs-engine (linked locally)
    player-three/             ← @base/player-three (linked locally)
    scene-builder/            ← @base/scene-builder (linked locally)
    camera-three/             ← @base/camera-three (linked locally)
    input/                    ← @base/input (linked locally)
    audio/                    ← @base/audio (linked locally)
  threejs-engine-dev/         ← THIS repo
  three-dreams/               ← Phase 4 game fork (sibling — Phase 4C blocked on Phase 3d)
```

## What This Harness Validates (Phase 3d)

- **Player locomotion:** grounded, airborne, water, recovery states via `@base/player-three`
- **Mixamo FBX pipeline:** semantic clip resolution, overlay system, `CharacterAnimationRig`
- **Scene authoring:** `SceneDescriptor` → `SceneBuilder` → `EditorSceneModule`
- **Swimming v1:** `SwimmableVolume`, tread/swim animation slots, shoulder-depth trigger
- **Camera strategies (Phase 3d):** third-person orbit + first-person eye-attach in editor play-sim

## Code Placement Rules

- Engine/package improvements → `SHARED/packages/<name>/`
- Scene authoring tools and harness scenes → `src/` in this repo
- Game-specific logic (rules, narrative) → `three-dreams/` — not here
- Shell improvements → `BASE/pwa-shell/`

## Stack

Vue 3 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind CSS · Vue Router · Pinia · Vite
Three.js · `@base/threejs-engine` · `@base/player-three` · `@base/scene-builder` · `@base/camera-three` · `@base/input` · `@base/audio`
